Corrente quadrada Chain is a unit of length equal to 66 feet it can be translated to Portuguese as \"Corrente\". It is subdivided into 100 Links (\"Elos\" in Portuguese) or 4 Rods (\"Cajados\" in Portuguese). Furlong (unit of length) and Rood (unit of area) have no translation to Portuguese.

Vara quadrada Rod is a unit of length equal to 16.5 feet, it can be better translated to Portuguese as \"Vara\" (instead of \"Cajado\" as stated before). Furlong (unit of length) and Rood (unit of area) have no translation to Portuguese.

EAU Dirham The United Arab Emirates dirham, also known as simply the Emirati dirham, is the currency of the United Arab Emirates. The term dirham is officially abbreviated \"AED\". By International standards ALL currencies have the form \"Country Currency\" (from English, the form will generate the international 3-letters abbreviation), only the country can be translated, such as \"Brazil Real\" and \"Brasil Real\" and \"BRL\".
